thread.title: 6 arrested after shots fired at NW Portland house party
thread.title_full: 6 arrested after shots fired at NW Portland house party | OregonLive.com

author: Elliot Njus | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: 6 arrested after shots fired at NW Portland house party
text:
A teen's party, held at his parents' Northwest Portland house while they were out of town, ended in gunfire and six arrests.
Washington County sheriff's deputies responding to 911 reports of gunfire in the 300 block of Northwest 88th Avenue found "numerous people" fleeing the house, according to a news release. Deputies who knocked on the door were initially denied entry by party host Payton Smith, 19, police said, but were later allowed in.
The party had been posted on Facebook, police said, and "grew to an unruly size." A fight broke out, and shots were fired at the house from outside. At least one shot struck the house, but no one was injured.
It's not clear who fired the shots, police said, but five people in a car stopped nearby were arrested.
Deputies arrested a 15-year-old boy on suspicion of theft after he told them he had taken a gun that matched casings found near the house. A 16-year-old boy was found with brass knuckles, police said, and arrested on suspicion of carrying a concealed weapon.
Jorge Perez, 23, of Portland, and a 15-year-old boy were arrested on probation violation warrants.
And Diamond T. Wilson, 20, of Portland, was arrested on suspicion of harassment in connection with the fight at the party.
Smith, the party host, was also arrested on suspicion of furnishing alcohol to minors.
